HEADWORD: Hamamelidaceae
<hw>Hamamelidaceae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A natural family of plants
comprising the genera <gen>Hamamelis</gen>; <gen>Corylopsis</gen>;
<gen>Fothergilla</gen>; <gen>Liquidambar</gen>; <gen>Parrotia</gen>; and
other small genera.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Hamamelidaceae</fam>, witch-hazel
family.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

